This is a submission for our clan member map for {cDS}, Cyber Death Squad.
For more information on this topic see:
http://cyberdeathsquad.com/forums/index.php?topic=8935.0

This map contains 4 sections, the front entrance, the art gallery, the loading dock and the upper level atrium.

Each of the "paintings" in the map would be replaced by a Steam ID tag from our members list, in the maps final format.  The map currently has our founders tags on a rotating cube in the center, as well as large version of our clan logo.  There is also one painting with my Steam ID tag inserted.

The art gallery is a maze setup, while the front and rear sections are straight through sniping zones.   The large upper atrium area is a shoot'em out section with only sparse cover.  The atrium also has jump down access into the gallery.

Questions remain on whether the map is too big for gungame.  We could remove any combination of the front, rear or atrium areas.
This map is the result of the combined effort of {cDS} members Stupor, The Black Rose, and winnebago_warrior.  credit to stupor for the original design first version of the map.

Just a close quarter's map that I did for my clan server.  But figured I would share it with everybody!

I was sick of how small gg_aim_shotty was so I based mine off of it (aka, built the entire thing myself, not like it was a complicated design), making it somewhat larger, better cover, more lighting, and added a basement to it.  

I used some brushwork from the cbble sdk map, but modified them all around to get it to work.  Was a good learning experience as well.

has 60 spawn points..  I wouldn't suggest that many people, but hey.. its there..  also has buyzones incase an update messes up GunGame.

This map was inspired by the time when I visited the volcanic caves in Oregon. Although the map itself is nothing like the caves, my only goal for this map was to make a map with caves in it. I think it turned out fairly well since both teams have an equal advantage in their own way.

I made it so the Terrorists have 1 more way to get into the caves than the Counter Terrorists do, but I put the lighting for the Counter Terrorists so that they could tell where they Terrorists were behind things such as rocks when the battle is taken above the caves.

This map is for upto 40 people. Although 40 would probably be a bit crouded on this map, it's worth a try if you have a server big enough for it.

This map was inspired by a 3d model of a castle and gg_churches. I have always wanted to make this map, but never had the time. I still don't but I needed to get it out of me lol. It's comprised of two castles, identical in construction but different in texture so you know where you are on the map. In between the castles is a garden maze where soldiers can use the bushes and large oak tree for cover before assaulting. On one side there is a tunnel breach and on the other is a wooden catwalk.
